& [ReplayInputState] is the BSD replay graph seed
  + [source_claim_node] is L-hand and R-hand source language suggests analytic collapse, rational growth, and a possible transfer between symbolic sides
  + [formal_object_node] is BSD requires equality between analytic rank and Mordell-Weil rank, with leading coefficient, regulator, local factors, and torsion controls in the full formula
  + [candidate_transfer_node] is Chow-Heegner, generalized Heegner-cycle, diagonal-cycle, rank-one Heegner, and higher-rank system routes may produce partial evidence or special-case structure
  + [boundary_lock_001_source_count] is no row currently provides a rank-parametrized source-count mechanism over the general target field
  + [boundary_lock_002_independence] is independence of produced points or cycles remains special, conditional, computational, or unknown outside calibrated cases
  + [boundary_lock_003_upper_control] is same-hypothesis upper control is not closed by the source-transfer routes
  + [proof_authority_node] is no route has authority to promote the source-transfer analogy into a general BSD proof

& [ReplayUpdateTrace] is the symbolic smoothing run
  + [step_001_measure] is high irregularity is concentrated where source-transfer language compresses source count, independence, upper control, and proof promotion into one proposition
  + [step_002_reweight] is source-backed support for special cases remains strong while unsupported general transfer edges are lowered
  + [step_003_split] is the compressed claim separates into source meaning, formal BSD target, candidate mechanism, sufficiency obligations, and boundary locks
  + [step_004_route] is the overclaim that special points or cycles solve general BSD is routed to explicit boundary nodes instead of being deleted
  + [step_005_stop] is the run stops after boundary clarity improves and no allowed smoothing step can close the mathematical locks

& [ValidationResults] is the first test result set
  + [test_001_replay] is passed_for_bsd_boundary_reconstruction
    = finding: the model reconstructs the source/formal/boundary separation already produced by the BSD sufficiency ledger
  + [test_002_overclaim_detection] is passed_for_special_case_to_general_proof_overclaim
    = finding: special Heegner-style and higher-cycle evidence is not promoted to general BSD authority
  + [test_003_trace_integrity] is passed_for_source_and_research_link_preservation
    = finding: replay nodes remain linked to the model specification and BSD sufficiency ledger
  + [test_004_metric_direction] is qualitatively_passed_without_numeric_runtime
    = finding: irregularity decreases by splitting the compressed claim, while distinction loss remains controlled

